Generating the HP filter figures in EViews from the Time Series dataset.
Software used: EViews 12 Student Version Lite for Mac (Student Edition - Feb 25 2025 Build)

Step1 Data import
First, importing the .csv file into EViews named "ent_spend_timeseries.csv". 

Step 2 Applying the HP Filter
HP Filter applied via GUI:
Method: Use Quick > Series Statistics > Hodrick-Prescott Filter
Lambda: 1600 (appropriate for quarterly data)

1. Total Entertainment Spending
All income groups
- Series: totent
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: tote_all

Low income group
- Series: totent_low
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: tote_low

High income group
- Series: totent_high
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: tote_high

Store output as: Trend components (tote_all, tote_low, tote_high)

2. Total Spending on Fees & Admissions
All income groups
- Series: tot_fa
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: totfa_all

Low income group
- Series: tot_fa_low
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: totfa_low

High income group
- Series: tot_fa_high
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: totfa_high

Store output as: Trend components (totfa_all, totfa_low, totfa_high)

3. Total Spending on TVs, Radio & Sound Equipment
All income groups
- Series: tot_tr
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: tottr_all

Low income group
- Series: tot_tr_low
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: tottr_low

High income group
- Series: tot_tr_high
- Lambda: 1600
- Output/Smoothed series: tottr_high

Store output as: Trend components (tottr_all, tottr_low, tottr_high)

Step 3 Visualization
Afterwards, grouping the 3 outputs per spending category and producing a simple line graph for each of them:
Create group with code:
group group_totfa totfa_all totfa_low totfa_high
group group_tottr tottr_all tottr_low tottr_high
group group_tote tote_all tote_low tote_high

Open the each group separately â†’ click View > Graph > Line to generate the comparison plot.

Export the graph via:
click Object > View Options > Copy to Clipboard 
